We have the great pleasure of being a part of the organizational team for Devsigner Conference. We are now in our 3rd year and our little conference has really gained some steam. It's excited to bring together not only industry leaders but esteemed colleagues, mentors, friends and a diverse community that is unified by the common love of all things Internet technology and design. Last year my close friend Peter Bliss did an impressive Session on 3D Printing technologies. Aside from that we attended a Session about Project Discovery given by my other close friend Tom Martin (who used to work for Grenade and shreds with the best of them) - we took away so many great tips! Thanks Tom! You rule! Then we tried on our first fully immersive VR Movie! Done. I'm sold. This year I personally spoke with a Web VR team member of Mozilla's Aframe framework - and he is seriously going to try and set up a session or workshop. I could not be more stoked on all the help we have had from our little community - with people like Micah Goldbot @micahgodbolt and Chris Martin @cmstudios to name a couple - your support is everything! Let's do this. Countdown to Devsigner Con 2016 is on! Session deadline is next week - so JOIN US - submit a session - share in the awesome.
